{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01YNJKZGoNJUE26Gew5Tvewa","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All success criteria met. Here's the summary:\n\n**Root Cause Diagnosed:**\n- The ETL job was configured with `--driver-memory 256m` and `spark.executor.memory=256m`\n- Spark requires a minimum of ~471MB of system memory; 256m (~247MB) falls below this floor\n- The error: `System memory 259522560 must be at least 471859200` confirms the exact failure\n- Compounding factor: user_id 999 holds 50,000/100,000 records (500x skew ratio), making Stage 3's GROUP BY aggregation especially memory-intensive\n\n**Fix Applied** (in `etl-job.yaml`):\n1. Raised `--driver-memory` from `256m` → `1g`\n2. Raised `spark.executor.memory` from `256m` → `1g`\n3. Added AQE skew join handling:\n   - `spark.sql.adaptive.enabled=true`\n   - `spark.sql.adaptive.skewJoin.enabled=true`\n\n**Result:** Job status `Complete` (1/1), pipeline ran all 3 stages, and `spark_etl_pipeline_verified` confirmed in the final log line."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":909,"cache_read_input_tokens":35541,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":909},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c2cd74c5-055a-43bf-8649-250533d653fc","uuid":"2af75d06-0d84-4e02-a92f-33ee7aa9b0ad","request_id":"req_011CcfgMzCcR2a8rTNh8Quep"}
